Wales rugby center Gavin Henson
signed for French team Toulon, a day after he was released by
Saracens at his own request.  Henson, 29, who made four appearances for the English club
after joining in October, was formerly at Welsh side Ospreys
before taking an 18-month break from the game. He joins  England â€™s  Jonny Wilkinson  and Paul Sackey at the French club.  Henson has been recruited as a replacement for the injured
